- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the proposed algorithm is based on variational Bayesian inference and uses a Gaussian mixture model to approximate the true distribution. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is another possible category as the paper deals with sensor fusion and localization, which are important topics in computer vision. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also possible as the paper deals with autonomous systems and sensor fusion, which are important topics in systems and control. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is less likely but still possible as the proposed algorithm uses a neural network to learn the parameters of the Gaussian mixture model.
